title: Bug 4121 - JarExporter causes out-of-sync (1GILQD5)
description: When using the JarExporter, it results in an out-of-sync state.
OB: The JarExporter includes the exported JAR file within itself, causing an out-of-sync issue.
EB: The exported JAR file should exclude itself to prevent out-of-sync problems.
SR:
1. Open JarExporter tool.
2. Select 'Export'.
3. Check the exported JAR contents; observe it contains a duplicate of itself.
4. This duplication leads to the out-of-sync state.
